    "actions_taken": [
      "Injured person evacuated to Terrebonne General Medical Center in Houma, Louisiana",
      "BSEE notification on 26 April 2021",
      "Investigation team gathered JSA, witness statements, photos, incident report, crane credentials, and inspection records",
      "Root Cause Analysis conducted by AES and Cantium"
    ],
    "summary": "On 24 April 2021 at approximately 1900 hrs, an employee of Alliance Energy Services, LLC was struck by a failed sling while assisting with removal of a Dry Hole Tree (DHT) from Well CA-30 at MP 41-CA. The sling, which was still attached to the DHT, became caught on a tubing hanger pin when the Liftboat Charleston was being raised to avoid rising sea state. The sling exceeded its capacity and broke, striking the injured person above the right elbow causing a 3-inch laceration. The incident resulted in a Lost Time Accident exceeding 3 days.",
